properties.NAME: Mt. Zion Blvd
properties.DESC: Current 2-lane road is under construction to covert to 3-lane section.  Current ADT (10,264).
properties.JUST: Currently, there is roughly a 50/50 split between traffic that continues on this section of road vs. traffic that takes Lake Harbin Rd (Minor Arterial) east to SR 42/Macon Hwy.

properties.NAME: Mt. Zion Blvd
properties.JUST: Traffic heading north/south between Jonesboro and Mt. Zion Blvd at I-75 (commercial shopping area) generally take this route as opposed to turning at intersection of Battle Creek Rd.

properties.NAME: Anvil Block Rd
properties.JUST: Recent nearby developments, including Walmart, Villages of Ellenwood S/D, and other distribution centers have increased volumes in this area.  Anvil Block is already identified as a Minor Arterial west of Stagecoach Rd.  Most of the traffic continues east-west on Anvil Block from/to Henry County as opposed to north/south via Stagecoach Rd.  This change will require an accompanying change for the section of Anvil Block in Henry County.

properties.NAME: Norman Dr
properties.DESC: Existing 2-Lane road currently undergoing construction to convert to 3-lane section.  Adjacent land uses include commercial shopping centers, a high school, church, and residential subdivisions and apartments.  ADT (7,438)
properties.JUST: Norman Dr. provides east-west connectivity between SR 314 and SR 139, both Minor Arterials.

properties.NAME: Tara Rd
properties.JUST: This road provides east-west connection between SR 920 (McDonough Rd) from/to Fayette County and US 19/41 (Tara Blvd).

properties.NAME: Flat Shoals Rd
properties.JUST: Flat Shoals Rd & Airport South Pkwy provide for the direct east-west movement connecting to SR 85.  Clayton will submit another request to convert Rock Hill Dr from Major Collector to Minor Collector.

properties.NAME: Garden Walk Blvd
properties.JUST: Proposed change from Local road to Urban Collector was previously approved by TCC on 1/6/12, TAQC on 1/12/12, and ARC Board on 1/25/12.

properties.NAME: Charles W. Grant Pkwy
properties.JUST: Multiple Lane roadway on Regional Thoroughfare Network serving east-west traffic to and from Atlanta Airport.  GDOT project 0001817 (June 2014 Let) will connect east-west traffic directly to/from Conley Road, resulting in increased volumes over the next few years.

properties.NAME: Southlake Pkwy
properties.JUST: Southlake Pkwy is an alternate to Jonesboro Rd/SR 54 (Minor Arterial) for north-southbound traffic and many travelers use this road due to adjacent high-density residential, governmental complexes to the south, schools, and access to I-75 to the north.

Flat Shoals Rd & Airport South Pkwy provide for the direct east-west movement connecting to SR 85.  Clayton will submit another request to convert Rock Hill Dr from Major Collector to Minor Collector.
properties.NAME: Airport South Pkwy
N. McDonough St.
properties.JUST: This route serves as an alternate to N. Main St and Jonesboro Rd for north-south travelers in/through Jonesboro and provides access to adjacent County governmental complexes.  This road should be converted to 5-Major Collector north of the intersection of SR 138, where ADT jumps to 13,346.

properties.NAME: Garden Walk Blvd
properties.JUST: Proposed change from Local road to Urban Collector was previously approved by TCC on 1/6/12, TAQC on 1/12/12, and ARC Board on 1/25/12.

properties.NAME: Phoenix Blvd
properties.JUST: Road services regional East-West traffic in northern part of County between Fulton Co and Henry Co as well as traffic to and from Atlanta Airport.  Connecting segments are Forest Pkwy (Minor Arterial) at SR 139 (Minor Arterial) and Godby Road (proposed upgrade to Major Collector) at SR 314 (Minor Arterial).

properties.NAME: Southlake Pkwy
properties.JUST: Southlake Pkwy is an alternate to Jonesboro Rd/SR 54 (Minor Arterial) for north-southbound traffic and many travelers use this road due to adjacent high-density residential, governmental complexes to the south, schools, and access to I-75 to the north.
Proposed change from Local road to Urban Collector was previously approved by TCC on 1/6/12, TAQC on 1/12/12, and ARC Board on 1/25/12.

properties.NAME: Upper Riverdale Rd
Rock Hill Dr
properties.JUST: Flat Shoals Rd & Airport South Pkwy provide for the direct east-west movement connecting to SR 85.  Rock Hill Dr. is used less frequently, therefore suggest downgrade to minor collector to indicate more accurate movement of traffic.  Flat Shoals Rd from Riverdale Rd to Flat Shoals/Rock Hill Dr intersection should remain a major collector.

properties.JUST: Provides east-west connection between Riverdale and Tara Blvd.  Also provides direct access to Southern Regional Medical Center and nearby medical offices.
